{"cp23":{"cp23:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp23'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp23:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp23:0.3":{"pli":"Nekkhammapāramī 3 ","eng":"The Perfection of Renunciation (3rd) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp23:0.4":{"pli":"Ayogharacariya ","eng":"Ayoghara’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp23:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:1.2":{"pli":"kāsirājassa atrajo; ","eng":"the true-born son of the king of Kāsi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:1.3":{"pli":"Ayogharamhi saṃvaḍḍho, ","eng":"I grew up in an iron house, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"For protection against <i lang='pi' translate='no'>yakkhas</i> who, according to <a href='index.html?q=ja510'>Ja 510</a>, are afraid of iron. As holdovers of the “old gods” they were threatened by the new technology of iron-smelting. "},"cp23:1.4":{"pli":"nāmenāsi ayogharo. ","eng":"so I was named Ayoghara. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:2.1":{"pli":"‘Dukkhena jīvito laddho, ","eng":"‘Your life has been a painful one, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:2.2":{"pli":"saṃpīḷe patiposito; ","eng":"as you’ve been raised in confinement. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:2.3":{"pli":"Ajjeva putta paṭipajja, ","eng":"Today, my son, rule ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:2.4":{"pli":"kevalaṃ vasudhaṃ imaṃ’. ","eng":"the entirety of this land.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:3.1":{"pli":"Saraṭṭhakaṃ sanigamaṃ, ","eng":"Having bowed to the citizens of country and town, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:3.2":{"pli":"sajanaṃ vanditva khattiyaṃ; ","eng":"the king and his people, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:3.3":{"pli":"Añjaliṃ paggahetvāna, ","eng":"I raised my joined palms ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:3.4":{"pli":"idaṃ vacanamabraviṃ. ","eng":"and said the following. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:4.1":{"pli":"‘Ye keci mahiyā sattā, ","eng":"‘All the creatures of this earth—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:4.2":{"pli":"hīnamukkaṭṭhamajjhimā; ","eng":"low, middle, or high—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:4.3":{"pli":"Nirārakkhā sake gehe, ","eng":"are unprotected in their own home, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:4.4":{"pli":"vaḍḍhanti sakañātibhi. ","eng":"in which they grew up with their families. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:5.1":{"pli":"Idaṃ loke uttariyaṃ, ","eng":"It was unique in the world ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Commentary has <i lang='pi' translate='no'>asadisaṁ</i>, <i lang='pi' translate='no'>āveṇikaṁ</i> for <i lang='pi' translate='no'>uttariya</i>. The expected sense “superior” doesn’t fit, unless it is sarcastic. "},"cp23:5.2":{"pli":"saṃpīḷe mama posanaṃ; ","eng":"to be raised in confinement. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:5.3":{"pli":"Ayogharamhi saṃvaḍḍho, ","eng":"I grew up in an iron house, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:5.4":{"pli":"appabhe candasūriye. ","eng":"scarcely lit by sun or moon. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:6.1":{"pli":"Pūtikuṇapasampuṇṇā, ","eng":"Filled with rotting carcass, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:6.2":{"pli":"muccitvā mātukucchito; ","eng":"I escaped my mother’s womb. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:6.3":{"pli":"Tato ghoratare dukkhe, ","eng":"Then to a viler suffering ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:6.4":{"pli":"puna pakkhittayoghare. ","eng":"I was tossed in an iron house. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:7.1":{"pli":"Yadihaṃ tādisaṃ patvā, ","eng":"Having fallen into such ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:7.2":{"pli":"dukkhaṃ paramadāruṇaṃ; ","eng":"appallingly dreadful suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:7.3":{"pli":"Rajjesu yadi rajjāmi, ","eng":"if I desired kingships, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:7.4":{"pli":"pāpānaṃ uttamo siyaṃ. ","eng":"I’d be the worst of the worst. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:8.1":{"pli":"Ukkaṇṭhitomhi kāyena, ","eng":"I’m fed up with the body, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"These lines were adapted from <a href='index.html?q=thag16.1#14.1'>Thag 16.1:14.1</a>. "},"cp23:8.2":{"pli":"rajjenamhi anatthiko; ","eng":"I have no need for kingship. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:8.3":{"pli":"Nibbutiṃ pariyesissaṃ, ","eng":"I shall seek quenching ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:8.4":{"pli":"yattha maṃ maccu na maddiye’. ","eng":"where Death will not crush me.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:9.1":{"pli":"Evāhaṃ cintayitvāna, ","eng":"Reflecting in this way, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:9.2":{"pli":"viravante mahājane; ","eng":"as the great crowd wailed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:9.3":{"pli":"Nāgova bandhanaṃ chetvā, ","eng":"like a bull elephant bursting his ropes, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:9.4":{"pli":"pāvisiṃ kānanaṃ vanaṃ. ","eng":"I entered the forest grove. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp23:10.1":{"pli":"Mātāpitā na me dessā, ","eng":"I had no dislike of my parents, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:10.2":{"pli":"napi me dessaṃ mahāyasaṃ; ","eng":"nor did I dislike the great fame. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:10.3":{"pli":"Sabbaññutaṃ piyaṃ mayhaṃ, ","eng":"But because omniscience is precious to me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp23:10.4":{"pli":"tasmā rajjaṃ pariccajin”ti. ","eng":"that is why I forsook kingship.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp23:11.1":{"pli":"Ayogharacariyaṃ tatiyaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp24":{"cp24:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp24'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp24:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp24:0.3":{"pli":"Nekkhammapāramī 4 ","eng":"The Perfection of Renunciation (4th) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp24:0.4":{"pli":"Bhisacariya ","eng":"The Conduct of the Lotus-eaters ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp24:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"According to <a href='index.html?q=ja488'>Ja 488</a> his name was Kañcana, “golden”. "},"cp24:1.2":{"pli":"kāsīnaṃ puravaruttame; ","eng":"in the capital citadel of Kāsi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:1.3":{"pli":"Bhaginī ca bhātaro satta, ","eng":"a sister and seven brothers ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:1.4":{"pli":"nibbattā sotthiye kule. ","eng":"were born in a learned family. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:2.1":{"pli":"Etesaṃ pubbajo āsiṃ, ","eng":"I was the first-born of them all, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:2.2":{"pli":"hirīsukkamupāgato; ","eng":"furnishing with pure conscience. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:2.3":{"pli":"Bhavaṃ disvāna bhayato, ","eng":"Seeing rebirth as fearful, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:2.4":{"pli":"nekkhammābhirato ahaṃ. ","eng":"I longed for renunciation. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:3.1":{"pli":"Mātāpitūhi pahitā, ","eng":"Sent for by my mother and father, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:3.2":{"pli":"sahāyā ekamānasā; ","eng":"my friends with one mind ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:3.3":{"pli":"Kāmehi maṃ nimantenti, ","eng":"invited me to enjoy sensual pleasures, saying: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:3.4":{"pli":"‘kulavaṃsaṃ dharehi’ti. ","eng":"‘Maintain the family lineage.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:4.1":{"pli":"Yaṃ tesaṃ vacanaṃ vuttaṃ, ","eng":"The words they said ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:4.2":{"pli":"gihīdhamme sukhāvahaṃ; ","eng":"about the ways a householder can find happiness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:4.3":{"pli":"Taṃ me ahosi kaṭhinaṃ, ","eng":"were hard for me to hear, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:4.4":{"pli":"tattaphālasamaṃ viya. ","eng":"like a heated ploughshare. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:5.1":{"pli":"Te maṃ tadā ukkhipantaṃ, ","eng":"When I turned down their proposal, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:5.2":{"pli":"pucchiṃsu patthitaṃ mama; ","eng":"they asked me what I wished for: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:5.3":{"pli":"‘Kiṃ tvaṃ patthayase samma, ","eng":"‘My dear, what is it that you wish, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:5.4":{"pli":"yadi kāme na bhuñjasi’. ","eng":"since you do not long for sensual pleasures?’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:6.1":{"pli":"Tesāhaṃ evamavacaṃ, ","eng":"I spoke to my beneficiaries, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:6.2":{"pli":"atthakāmo hitesinaṃ; ","eng":"wanting what is best. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:6.3":{"pli":"‘Nāhaṃ patthemi gihībhāvaṃ, ","eng":"‘I wish not for the householder’s state, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:6.4":{"pli":"nekkhammābhirato ahaṃ’. ","eng":"I long for renunciation.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:7.1":{"pli":"Te mayhaṃ vacanaṃ sutvā, ","eng":"Hearing my words, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:7.2":{"pli":"pitu mātu ca sāvayuṃ; ","eng":"they told my mother and father . ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:7.3":{"pli":"Mātāpitā evamāhu, ","eng":"My parents said this: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:7.4":{"pli":"‘sabbeva pabbajāma bho’. ","eng":"‘Sirs, let all of us go forth!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp24:8.1":{"pli":"Ubho mātāpitā mayhaṃ, ","eng":"So both my mother and father, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"In <a href='index.html?q=ja488'>Ja 488</a> he renounced only after the parents died. "},"cp24:8.2":{"pli":"bhaginī ca satta bhātaro; ","eng":"sister and seven brothers, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:8.3":{"pli":"Amitadhanaṃ chaḍḍayitvā, ","eng":"discarding countless riches, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp24:8.4":{"pli":"pāvisimhā mahāvanan”ti. ","eng":"entered the great forest.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>","comm":"This is only the preliminary to the Jātaka. They eventually are reduced to eating only lotus stalks, hence the title. "},"cp24:9.1":{"pli":"Bhisacariyaṃ catutthaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp25":{"cp25:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp25'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp25:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp25:0.3":{"pli":"Nekkhammapāramī 5 ","eng":"The Perfection of Renunciation (5th) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp25:0.4":{"pli":"Soṇapaṇḍitacariya ","eng":"Soṇa the Astute’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp25:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:1.2":{"pli":"nagare brahmavaḍḍhane; ","eng":"in the city of Brahmavaḍḍhana, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"“The Flourishing of Brahmā” was, according to the commentary, an alternate name for Benares. "},"cp25:1.3":{"pli":"Tattha kulavare seṭṭhe, ","eng":"I was reborn there ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:1.4":{"pli":"mahāsāle ajāyahaṃ. ","eng":"in a fine, wealthy, and eminent family. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp25:2.1":{"pli":"Tadāpi lokaṃ disvāna, ","eng":"Even so, I saw that the world ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:2.2":{"pli":"Andhībhūtaṃ tamotthaṭaṃ; ","eng":"had become blind, smothered in darkness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:2.3":{"pli":"Cittaṃ bhavato patikuṭati, ","eng":"My mind recoiled from rebirth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:2.4":{"pli":"Tuttavegahataṃ viya. ","eng":"as if harshly pricked by a goad. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp25:3.1":{"pli":"Disvāna vividhaṃ pāpaṃ, ","eng":"Seeing the many forms of wickedness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:3.2":{"pli":"evaṃ cintesahaṃ tadā; ","eng":"I though to myself: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:3.3":{"pli":"‘Kadāhaṃ gehā nikkhamma, ","eng":"‘When shall I leave the house ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:3.4":{"pli":"pavisissāmi kānanaṃ’. ","eng":"and enter the forest?’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp25:4.1":{"pli":"Tadāpi maṃ nimantesuṃ, ","eng":"Then too my relatives invited me ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:4.2":{"pli":"kāmabhogehi ñātayo; ","eng":"to enjoy the pleasures of the senses. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:4.3":{"pli":"Tesampi chandamācikkhiṃ, ","eng":"I told them of my desire, saying, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:4.4":{"pli":"‘mā nimantetha tehi maṃ’. ","eng":"‘Do not invite me to such things!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp25:5.1":{"pli":"Yo me kaniṭṭhako bhātā, ","eng":"My younger brother, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:5.2":{"pli":"nando nāmāsi paṇḍito; ","eng":"who was named Nanda the astute, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:5.3":{"pli":"Sopi maṃ anusikkhanto, ","eng":"followed my ethical practices, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:5.4":{"pli":"pabbajjaṃ samarocayi. ","eng":"and chose to go forth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Horner’s “found equal pleasure” for <i lang='pi' translate='no'>samarocayi</i> is wrong. It occurs at <a href='index.html?q=thig13.4#11.2'>Thig 13.4:11.2</a> and <a href='index.html?q=snp3.1#1.4'>Snp 3.1:1.4</a> where it simply describes the decision to go forth. "},"cp25:6.1":{"pli":"Ahaṃ soṇo ca nando ca, ","eng":"I, Soṇa, and Nanda, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:6.2":{"pli":"ubho mātāpitā mama; ","eng":"and both my mother and father, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:6.3":{"pli":"Tadāpi bhoge chaḍḍetvā, ","eng":"then discarded our riches ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp25:6.4":{"pli":"pāvisimhā mahāvanan”ti. ","eng":"entered the great forest.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp25:7.1":{"pli":"Soṇapaṇḍitacariyaṃ pañcamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp26":{"cp26:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp26'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp26:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp26:0.3":{"pli":"Adiṭṭhānapāramī 1 ","eng":"The Perfection of Resolve ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp26:0.4":{"pli":"Temiyacariya ","eng":"Temiya’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp26:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:1.2":{"pli":"kāsirājassa atrajo; ","eng":"the true-born son of the king of Kāsi, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:1.3":{"pli":"Mūgapakkhoti nāmena, ","eng":"Mūgapakkha was my name, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"“Dumb and Crippled”. "},"cp26:1.4":{"pli":"temiyoti vadanti maṃ. ","eng":"they called me Temiya. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:2.1":{"pli":"Soḷasitthisahassānaṃ, ","eng":"None of the sixteen thousand court women ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:2.2":{"pli":"na vijjati pumo tadā; ","eng":"had given birth to a male. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:2.3":{"pli":"Ahorattānaṃ accayena, ","eng":"After many days and nights ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:2.4":{"pli":"nibbatto ahamekako. ","eng":"I was born, the only one. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:3.1":{"pli":"Kicchā laddhaṃ piyaṃ puttaṃ, ","eng":"To my father I was a dear son born with difficulty, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:3.2":{"pli":"abhijātaṃ jutindharaṃ; ","eng":"a light-bringer of impeccable lineage. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:3.3":{"pli":"Setacchattaṃ dhārayitvāna, ","eng":"Holding a white umbrella over my bed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:3.4":{"pli":"sayane poseti maṃ pitā. ","eng":"my father provided for me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:4.1":{"pli":"Niddāyamāno sayanavare, ","eng":"Sleeping on the fine bed, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:4.2":{"pli":"Pabujjhitvānahaṃ tadā; ","eng":"then having awoken, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:4.3":{"pli":"Addasaṃ paṇḍaraṃ chattaṃ, ","eng":"I saw the pale umbrella, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:4.4":{"pli":"Yenāhaṃ nirayaṃ gato. ","eng":"by which I had gone to hell. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"According to <a href='index.html?q=ja538'>Ja 538</a>, seeing his father meting out cruel punishments, he realized that the umbrella of royal authority meant that one day he would have to do the same and suffer the consequences. "},"cp26:5.1":{"pli":"Saha diṭṭhassa me chattaṃ, ","eng":"At the sight of the umbrella ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:5.2":{"pli":"tāso uppajji bheravo; ","eng":"a terrible dread arose in me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:5.3":{"pli":"Vinicchayaṃ samāpanno, ","eng":"I reached the decision, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:5.4":{"pli":"‘kathāhaṃ imaṃ muñcissaṃ’. ","eng":"‘How can I be free of this?’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:6.1":{"pli":"Pubbasālohitā mayhaṃ, ","eng":"A former blood-relation of mine, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:6.2":{"pli":"devatā atthakāminī; ","eng":"a goddess wishing to help, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"This phrase is identical with <a href='index.html?q=snp5.1#11.2'>Snp 5.1:11.2</a>. "},"cp26:6.3":{"pli":"Sā maṃ disvāna dukkhitaṃ, ","eng":"saw my suffering ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:6.4":{"pli":"tīsu ṭhānesu yojayi. ","eng":"and enjoined me to three states. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:7.1":{"pli":"‘Mā paṇḍiccayaṃ vibhāvaya, ","eng":"‘Don’t show intelligence, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:7.2":{"pli":"Bālamato bhava sabbapāṇinaṃ; ","eng":"be as a fool to all creatures, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:7.3":{"pli":"Sabbo taṃ jano ocināyatu, ","eng":"let all folk scorn you, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:7.4":{"pli":"Evaṃ tava attho bhavissati’. ","eng":"thus you will achieve your goal.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:8.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ vuttāyahaṃ tassā, ","eng":"When she had spoken, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:8.2":{"pli":"idaṃ vacanamabraviṃ; ","eng":"I said the following. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:8.3":{"pli":"‘Karomi te taṃ vacanaṃ, ","eng":"‘I shall do your bidding, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:8.4":{"pli":"yaṃ tvaṃ bhaṇasi devate; ","eng":"just as you say, goddess. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:8.5":{"pli":"Atthakāmāsi me amma, ","eng":"You want what’s best for me, mom, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"She was his mother in a past life. "},"cp26:8.6":{"pli":"hitakāmāsi devate’. ","eng":"you desire my welfare, goddess.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:9.1":{"pli":"Tassāhaṃ vacanaṃ sutvā, ","eng":"After hearing her words, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:9.2":{"pli":"sāgareva thalaṃ labhiṃ; ","eng":"I was like one lost at sea reaching the shore. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:9.3":{"pli":"Haṭṭho saṃviggamānaso, ","eng":"I was thrilled, my mind elated, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:9.4":{"pli":"tayo aṅge adhiṭṭhahiṃ. ","eng":"and I resolved on three factors. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:10.1":{"pli":"Mūgo ahosiṃ badhiro, ","eng":"I became deaf, and dumb, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:10.2":{"pli":"pakkho gativivajjito; ","eng":"and crippled, unable to walk. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:10.3":{"pli":"Ete aṅge adhiṭṭhāya, ","eng":"Resolving on these factors, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:10.4":{"pli":"vassāni soḷasaṃ vasiṃ. ","eng":"I lived for sixteen years. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:11.1":{"pli":"Tato me hatthapāde ca, ","eng":"Then they rubbed my hands and feet, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:11.2":{"pli":"jivhaṃ sotañca maddiya; ","eng":"my tongue and ears as well, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:11.3":{"pli":"Anūnataṃ me passitvā, ","eng":"and seeing no defect in me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:11.4":{"pli":"‘kāḷakaṇṇī’ti nindisuṃ. ","eng":"denounced me as ‘black-ear’. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Kāḷakaṇṇī</i> is an odd term meaning “unlucky one”. It is also a name of a dark goddess opposed to Siri, goddess of luck. Could this imply that he had a dark goddess whispering in his ear? "},"cp26:12.1":{"pli":"Tato jānapadā sabbe, ","eng":"Due to that, the entire country, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:12.2":{"pli":"senāpatipurohitā; ","eng":"including the generals and priests, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:12.3":{"pli":"Sabbe ekamanā hutvā, ","eng":"with one mind ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:12.4":{"pli":"chaḍḍanaṃ anumodisuṃ. ","eng":"cheered as I was discarded. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:13.1":{"pli":"Sohaṃ tesaṃ matiṃ sutvā, ","eng":"When I heard of their decision ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:13.2":{"pli":"haṭṭho saṃviggamānaso; ","eng":"I was thrilled, my mind elated, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:13.3":{"pli":"‘Yassatthāya tapociṇṇo, ","eng":"‘The goal for which I lived fervently ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:13.4":{"pli":"so me attho samijjhatha’. ","eng":"I have achieved.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:14.1":{"pli":"Nhāpetvā anulimpitvā, ","eng":"Bathed and oiled, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"On the queen’s intercession, he was granted seven days ceremonial kingship. "},"cp26:14.2":{"pli":"veṭhetvā rājaveṭhanaṃ; ","eng":"with my turban wrapped, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:14.3":{"pli":"Chattena abhisiñcitvā, ","eng":"anointed, they held the umbrella ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:14.4":{"pli":"kāresuṃ puraṃ padakkhiṇaṃ. ","eng":"as they paraded me around the city. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:15.1":{"pli":"Sattāhaṃ dhārayitvāna, ","eng":"After the seventh day holding the umbrella, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:15.2":{"pli":"uggate ravimaṇḍale; ","eng":"when the sun’s orb had risen, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:15.3":{"pli":"Rathena maṃ nīharitvā, ","eng":"I was taken out by chariot, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:15.4":{"pli":"sārathī vanamupāgami. ","eng":"until the charioteer came to a wood. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:16.1":{"pli":"Ekokāse rathaṃ katvā, ","eng":"Leaving the chariot in the open, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:16.2":{"pli":"sajjassaṃ hatthamuccito; ","eng":"the bridled horse released from his hand, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:16.3":{"pli":"Sārathī khaṇatī kāsuṃ, ","eng":"the charioteer dug a pit ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:16.4":{"pli":"nikhātuṃ pathaviyā mamaṃ. ","eng":"to bury me in the ground. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:17.1":{"pli":"Adhiṭṭhitamadhiṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"I was afraid for the many different ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:17.2":{"pli":"tajjento vividhakāraṇā; ","eng":"resolves that I had undertaken, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:17.3":{"pli":"Na bhindiṃ tamadhiṭṭhānaṃ, ","eng":"so I did not break that resolve, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:17.4":{"pli":"bodhiyāyeva kāraṇā. ","eng":"because it was solely for awakening. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:18.1":{"pli":"Mātāpitā na me dessā, ","eng":"I had no dislike of my parents, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:18.2":{"pli":"attā me na ca dessiyo; ","eng":"nor did I dislike myself. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:18.3":{"pli":"Sabbaññutaṃ piyaṃ mayhaṃ, ","eng":"But because omniscience is precious to me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:18.4":{"pli":"tasmā vatamadhiṭṭhahiṃ. ","eng":"that is why I resolved on my vow. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp26:19.1":{"pli":"Ete aṅge adhiṭṭhāya, ","eng":"Having resolved the three factors, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:19.2":{"pli":"Vassāni soḷasaṃ vasiṃ; ","eng":"I lived for sixteen years. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:19.3":{"pli":"Adhiṭṭhānena me samo natthi, ","eng":"There is no-one to equal my resolve: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp26:19.4":{"pli":"Esā me adhiṭṭhānapāramī”ti. ","eng":"this is my perfection of resolve.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp26:20.1":{"pli":"Temiyacariyaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp27":{"cp27:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp27'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp27:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp27:0.3":{"pli":"Saccapāramī 1 ","eng":"The Perfection of Truth (1st) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp27:0.4":{"pli":"Kapirājacariya ","eng":"The Monkey King’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp27:1.1":{"pli":"“Yadā ahaṃ kapi āsiṃ, ","eng":"“When I was a monkey ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:1.2":{"pli":"nadīkūle darīsaye; ","eng":"in a cleft on the riverbank, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:1.3":{"pli":"Pīḷito susumārena, ","eng":"harassed by a crocodile ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:1.4":{"pli":"gamanaṃ na labhāmahaṃ. ","eng":"I could not get across. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp27:2.1":{"pli":"Yamhokāse ahaṃ ṭhatvā, ","eng":"Where I used to land ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:2.2":{"pli":"orā pāraṃ patāmahaṃ; ","eng":"when jumping from the near shore to the far, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:2.3":{"pli":"Tatthacchi sattu vadhako, ","eng":"there crouched my deadly foe, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:2.4":{"pli":"kumbhīlo luddadassano. ","eng":"the baleful gharial. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp27:3.1":{"pli":"So maṃ asaṃsi ‘ehī’ti, ","eng":"Reassuring me, he said ‘Come!’ ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:3.2":{"pli":"‘ahampemī’ti taṃ vatiṃ; ","eng":"‘I am coming,’ I said to him. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:3.3":{"pli":"Tassa matthakamakkamma, ","eng":"Stepping on his head ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:3.4":{"pli":"parakūle patiṭṭhahiṃ. ","eng":"I made it to the far bank. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp27:4.1":{"pli":"Na tassa alikaṃ bhaṇitaṃ, ","eng":"I spoke no lie to him, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:4.2":{"pli":"yathā vācaṃ akāsahaṃ; ","eng":"but acted according to my word. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:4.3":{"pli":"Saccena me samo natthi, ","eng":"There is no-one to equal my truthfulness: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp27:4.4":{"pli":"esā me saccapāramī”ti. ","eng":"this is my perfection of truth.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp27:4.5":{"pli":"Kapirājacariyaṃ sattamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp28":{"cp28:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp28'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp28:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp28:0.3":{"pli":"Saccapāramī 2 ","eng":"The Perfection of Truth (2nd) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp28:0.4":{"pli":"Saccatāpasacariya ","eng":"The Ascetic Truthful’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp28:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp28:1.2":{"pli":"Tāpaso saccasavhayo; ","eng":"an ascetic known as Truthful, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp28:1.3":{"pli":"Saccena lokaṃ pālesiṃ, ","eng":"I protected the world with my truth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp28:1.4":{"pli":"Samaggaṃ janamakāsahan”ti. ","eng":"uniting the people.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>","comm":"This alludes to <a href='index.html?q=ja73'>Ja 73</a> Saccaṁkirajātaka. "},"cp28:2.1":{"pli":"Saccatāpasacariyaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp29":{"cp29:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp29'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp29:0.2":{"pli":"Yudhañjayavagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Yudhañjaya ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp29:0.3":{"pli":"Saccapāramī 3 ","eng":"The Perfection of Truth (3rd) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp29:0.4":{"pli":"Vaṭṭapotakacariya ","eng":"The Baby Quail’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp29:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I was ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:1.2":{"pli":"magadhe vaṭṭapotako; ","eng":"a baby quail in Magadha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:1.3":{"pli":"Ajātapakkho taruṇo, ","eng":"I was young, with wings unsprouted, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:1.4":{"pli":"maṃsapesi kulāvake. ","eng":"just a scrap of meat in the nest. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:2.1":{"pli":"Mukhatuṇḍakenāharitvā, ","eng":"With food she brought in her beak ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:2.2":{"pli":"mātā posayatī mamaṃ; ","eng":"my mother nurtured me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:2.3":{"pli":"Tassā phassena jīvāmi, ","eng":"I survived through her touch, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:2.4":{"pli":"natthi me kāyikaṃ balaṃ. ","eng":"for I had no physical strength. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:3.1":{"pli":"Saṃvacchare gimhasamaye, ","eng":"One year, in the hot season, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:3.2":{"pli":"davaḍāho padippati; ","eng":"the forest caught fire. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:3.3":{"pli":"Upagacchati amhākaṃ, ","eng":"It came towards us, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:3.4":{"pli":"pāvako kaṇhavattanī. ","eng":"a conflagration with a blackened trail. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:4.1":{"pli":"Dhamadhamāiti evaṃ, ","eng":"The fire roared and rumbled ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:4.2":{"pli":"saddāyanto mahāsikhī; ","eng":"with great crests of flame, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:4.3":{"pli":"Anupubbena jhāpento, ","eng":"gradually burning ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:4.4":{"pli":"aggi mamamupāgami. ","eng":"closer to me. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:5.1":{"pli":"Aggivegabhayātītā, ","eng":"Alarmed and terrified at the fierce fire, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:5.2":{"pli":"tasitā mātāpitā mama; ","eng":"my mother and father ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:5.3":{"pli":"Kulāvake maṃ chaḍḍetvā, ","eng":"abandoned me in the nest, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:5.4":{"pli":"attānaṃ parimocayuṃ. ","eng":"saving themselves. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:6.1":{"pli":"Pāde pakkhe pajahāmi, ","eng":"I beat my feet and wings, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Text’s <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pajahāmi</i> does not seem to fit. Commentary notes variant readings <i lang='pi' translate='no'>paṭīhāmi</i> and <i lang='pi' translate='no'>patīhāmi</i> from <i lang='pi' translate='no'>īhati</i> “to endeavor, to strive”. "},"cp29:6.2":{"pli":"natthi me kāyikaṃ balaṃ; ","eng":"but I had no physical strength. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:6.3":{"pli":"Sohaṃ agatiko tattha, ","eng":"When unable to leave, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:6.4":{"pli":"evaṃ cintesahaṃ tadā. ","eng":"I thought this there: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:7.1":{"pli":"‘Yesāhaṃ upadhāveyyaṃ, ","eng":"‘Those to whom I ought to run, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:7.2":{"pli":"bhīto tasitavedhito; ","eng":"scared and trembling with fear, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:7.3":{"pli":"Te maṃ ohāya pakkantā, ","eng":"have escaped, leaving me behind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:7.4":{"pli":"kathaṃ me ajja kātave. ","eng":"How should I act today? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:8.1":{"pli":"Atthi loke sīlaguṇo, ","eng":"There is the quality of virtue in the world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:8.2":{"pli":"saccaṃ soceyyanuddayā; ","eng":"truth, purity, and mercy. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:8.3":{"pli":"Tena saccena kāhāmi, ","eng":"By this truth I will make ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:8.4":{"pli":"saccakiriyamuttamaṃ. ","eng":"a supreme declaration of truth.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:9.1":{"pli":"Āvejjetvā dhammabalaṃ, ","eng":"Inspired by the power of Dhamma, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:9.2":{"pli":"saritvā pubbake jine; ","eng":"recollecting the former Victors, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:9.3":{"pli":"Saccabalamavassāya, ","eng":"relying on the power of truth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:9.4":{"pli":"saccakiriyamakāsahaṃ. ","eng":"I made a declaration of truth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:10.1":{"pli":"Santi pakkhā apatanā, ","eng":"‘I have wings that do not fly! ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Me</i> is elided in these lines, per commentary. "},"cp29:10.2":{"pli":"santi pādā avañcanā; ","eng":"I have feet that do not walk! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:10.3":{"pli":"Mātāpitā ca nikkhantā, ","eng":"Mother and father have fled! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:10.4":{"pli":"jātaveda paṭikkama’. ","eng":"Jātaveda the fire: go back!’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp29:11.1":{"pli":"Sahasacce kate mayhaṃ, ","eng":"As I declared this truth ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:11.2":{"pli":"Mahāpajjalito sikhī; ","eng":"the great crested flames ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:11.3":{"pli":"Vajjesi soḷasakarīsāni, ","eng":"withdrew sixteen leagues, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:11.4":{"pli":"Udakaṃ patvā yathā sikhī; ","eng":"as if they had come to water. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:11.5":{"pli":"Saccena me samo natthi, ","eng":"There is no-one to equal my truthfulness: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp29:11.6":{"pli":"Esā me saccapāramī”ti. ","eng":"this is my perfection of truth.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp29:12.1":{"pli":"Vaṭṭapotakacariyaṃ navamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"cp3":{"cp3:0.1":{"pli":"Cariyāpiṭaka ","eng":"The Conduct Leading to Buddhahood ","html":"<article id='cp3'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li>"},"cp3:0.2":{"pli":"Akittivagga ","eng":"The Chapter With Akitti ","html":"<li>{}</li>"},"cp3:0.3":{"pli":"Dānapāramī 3 ","eng":"The Perfection of Giving (3rd) ","html":"<li>{}</li></ul>"},"cp3:0.4":{"pli":"Kururājacariya ","eng":"Kururāja’s Conduct ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"cp3:1.1":{"pli":"“Punāparaṃ yadā homi, ","eng":"“Then again when I reigned ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:1.2":{"pli":"indapatthe puruttame; ","eng":"in Indapatta, the capital city, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Indrapastha, modern Delhi. "},"cp3:1.3":{"pli":"Rājā dhanañcayo nāma, ","eng":"as the king named Dhanañjaya ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:1.4":{"pli":"kusale dasahupāgato. ","eng":"I was blessed with the ten skillful deeds. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:2.1":{"pli":"Kaliṅgaraṭṭhavisayā, ","eng":"From the realm of Kaliṅga ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:2.2":{"pli":"brāhmaṇā upagañchu maṃ; ","eng":"brahmins came to me ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:2.3":{"pli":"Āyācuṃ maṃ hatthināgaṃ, ","eng":"requesting the royal elephant ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:2.4":{"pli":"dhaññaṃ maṅgalasammataṃ. ","eng":"that was lucky and deemed auspicious. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:3.1":{"pli":"‘Avuṭṭhiko janapado, ","eng":"‘Our nation is suffering from drought, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:3.2":{"pli":"dubbhikkho chātako mahā; ","eng":"food is scarce and famine abounds, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:3.3":{"pli":"Dadāhi pavaraṃ nāgaṃ, ","eng":"please give the noble elephant ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:3.4":{"pli":"nīlaṃ añjanasavhayaṃ’. ","eng":"of midnight hue named Añjana.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:4.1":{"pli":"‘Na me yācakamanuppatte, ","eng":"‘When supplicants come to me ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:4.2":{"pli":"paṭikkhepo anucchavo; ","eng":"it is unbefitting to refuse. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:4.3":{"pli":"Mā me bhijji samādānaṃ, ","eng":"Let not my vow be broken, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:4.4":{"pli":"dassāmi vipulaṃ gajaṃ’. ","eng":"I shall give the mighty elephant.’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:5.1":{"pli":"Nāgaṃ gahetvā soṇḍāya, ","eng":"Taking the elephant by the trunk, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:5.2":{"pli":"bhiṅgāre ratanāmaye; ","eng":"and a bejeweled ceremonial vessel, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:5.3":{"pli":"Jalaṃ hatthe ākiritvā, ","eng":"I sprinkled water on the hand, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:5.4":{"pli":"brāhmaṇānaṃ adaṃ gajaṃ. ","eng":"and gave the elephant to the brahmins. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:6.1":{"pli":"Tassa nāge padinnamhi, ","eng":"When I had given the elephant, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:6.2":{"pli":"amaccā etadabravuṃ; ","eng":"my ministers said, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:6.3":{"pli":"‘Kiṃ nu tuyhaṃ varaṃ nāgaṃ, ","eng":"‘Why did you give the noble elephant ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:6.4":{"pli":"yācakānaṃ padassasi. ","eng":"to the supplicants? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:7.1":{"pli":"Dhaññaṃ maṅgalasampannaṃ, ","eng":"He was lucky and endowed with the auspicious, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:7.2":{"pli":"saṅgāmavijayuttamaṃ; ","eng":"supreme victor in battle. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:7.3":{"pli":"Tasmiṃ nāge padinnamhi, ","eng":"Now you have given the elephant, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:7.4":{"pli":"kiṃ te rajjaṃ karissati’. ","eng":"how shall you govern the realm?’ ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"cp3:8.1":{"pli":"‘Rajjampi me dade sabbaṃ, ","eng":"‘I would give the entire realm ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:8.2":{"pli":"sarīraṃ dajjamattano; ","eng":"and my physical body as well. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:8.3":{"pli":"Sabbaññutaṃ piyaṃ mayhaṃ, ","eng":"Omniscience is precious to me, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"cp3:8.4":{"pli":"tasmā nāgaṃ adāsahan’”ti. ","eng":"which is why I gave away the elephant.’” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"cp3:9.1":{"pli":"Kururājacariyaṃ tatiyaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}